  "text": "Module resolution in TypeScript is primarily implemented in **src/compiler/moduleNameResolver.ts** (~3400+ lines), with supporting types in types.ts, pattern matching utilities in utilities.ts and core.ts, and call-site orchestration in program.ts and resolutionCache.ts.\n\n**Entry point & strategy dispatch**: `resolveModuleName` (line 1401) is the main entry. It reads `ModuleResolutionKind` from compiler options and dispatches via a switch (lines 1434-1452) to: `node16ModuleNameResolver` (Node16), `nodeNextModuleNameResolver` (NodeNext), `nodeModuleNameResolver` (Node10/legacy), `bundlerModuleNameResolver` (Bundler), or `classicNameResolver` (Classic).\n\n**Node16/NodeNext resolution**: `node16ModuleNameResolver` (line 1704) and `nodeNextModuleNameResolver` (line 1717) both delegate to `nodeNextModuleNameResolverWorker` (line 1730), which configures `NodeResolutionFeatures` (enum at line 1682) including Exports, Imports, SelfName, and ExportsPatternTrailers. The worker calls `nodeModuleNameResolverWorker` (line 1795).\n\n**Package.json exports resolution**: `loadModuleFromExports` (line 2613) reads `package.json#exports`, `loadModuleFromExportsOrImports` (line 2702) handles the lookup table traversal, and `getLoadModuleFromTargetExportOrImport` (line 2745) resolves individual export/import targets with conditional matching. `loadModuleFromImports` (line 2650) handles `#imports`, `loadModuleFromSelfNameReference` (line 2575) handles self-referencing.\n\n**Classic resolver**: `classicNameResolver` (line 3250) implements the legacy resolution without node_modules walking.\n\n**getPackageJsonInfo**: Two variants exist - a cache-lookup closure (line 1049) and the main function (line 2440) that reads and caches package.json data. `getPackageScopeForPath` (line 2394) walks ancestor directories to find the enclosing package scope.\n\n**Path pattern matching**: `matchPatternOrExact` in utilities.ts (line 10200) matches path-mapped module names against `paths` patterns. `findBestPatternMatch` in core.ts (line 2410) finds the longest-prefix pattern match, and `isPatternMatch` (line 2445) checks individual prefix+suffix patterns.\n\n**Tracing/diagnostics**: `trace` (line 115) and `isTraceEnabled` (line 120) are the low-level trace utilities. `traceIfEnabled` (line 3407) is a convenience wrapper. Diagnostic messages from `Diagnostics.*` are used extensively (~102 trace/diagnostic references) throughout resolution to report failures, matched patterns, resolution kinds, and package.json interpretation.",
